cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper proposes a method for classifying cervical cells based on deep features using convolutional neural networks (ConvNets). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques and the evaluation of the proposed method on benchmark datasets suggest that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
